This is a highly plausible reaction pair. Aryl iodides are excellent substrates for Suzuki couplings. Both reactants are stable and the reaction should be chemoselective, as the C-F bond on the boronic acid partner is unreactive under typical conditions.

This is a plausible reaction pair with modern catalytic systems. While aryl chlorides are less reactive than bromides or iodides, numerous palladium catalysts with specialized phosphine ligands (e.g., Buchwald or Fu type ligands) can efficiently mediate this transformation.
